Bottom Line: Firebase handles ~80% of Lifestream’s infrastructure natively. The only external dependencies worth adding are Memorystore (Redis for queue ordering) and Cloud SQL (PostgreSQL for relational audit logs). Everything else — auth, real-time sync, offline, push, file storage, serverless logic — lives entirely within the Firebase/GCP ecosystem. Firebase Studio is an ideal environment to prototype Phases 1 and 2 before any app store submission.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​
